The paper presents a new type of mixture model that can be applied to various types of data, including text and 3D object arrangements. Therefore, it could fit into several arXiv CS sub-categories. The most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper focuses on learning and inference algorithms for the proposed models. The second likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as the paper presents a new approach to modeling data that could be useful in various AI applications. The third likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision), as the paper includes an application of the proposed models to learning 3D object arrangements. The fourth likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), as the paper also includes an application of the proposed models to topic modeling. Finally, the fifth likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), as the proposed models could be applied to network data.
